        "content": "<p>Some ideas:</p>\n<p>You can decompose a topos into locale slices: for each object <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> in the topos <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">E</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathcal{E}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.08944em;\">E</span></span></span></span> you can write <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>L</mi><mi>X</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">L_X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">L</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3283em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> for the localic reflection of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathcal{E}/X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.08944em;\">E</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> (its opens correspond to the subobjects of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span>). There is a geometric morphism<br>\n<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>i</mi><mi>X</mi></msub><mo>:</mo><msub><mi>L</mi><mi>X</mi></msub><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">E</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">i_X : L_X \\to \\mathcal{E}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8095em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3283em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">L</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3283em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.08944em;\">E</span></span></span></span><br>\nfor each <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span>. The pullback <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msubsup><mi>i</mi><mi>X</mi><mo>∗</mo></msubsup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">i_X^*</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.964em;vertical-align:-0.2753em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.6887em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.4247em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mbin mtight\">∗</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2753em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> restricts a sheaf to the frame of subobjects of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<p>The family of the <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>i</mi><mi>X</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">i_X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8095em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3283em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>'s is jointly surjective: if there are two objects <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>G</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">G</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span></span></span></span> in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">E</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathcal{E}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.08944em;\">E</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msubsup><mi>i</mi><mi>X</mi><mo>∗</mo></msubsup><mi>F</mi><mo>≅</mo><msubsup><mi>i</mi><mi>X</mi><mo>∗</mo></msubsup><mi>G</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">i_X^*F \\cong i_X^*G</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.964em;vertical-align:-0.2753em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.6887em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.4247em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mbin mtight\">∗</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2753em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≅</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.964em;vertical-align:-0.2753em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.6887em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.4247em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mbin mtight\">∗</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2753em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span></span></span></span> for each <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> then <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo>≅</mo><mi>G</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F \\cong G</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≅</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<p>Now for two geometric morphisms <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ϕ</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>ψ</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">E</mi><mo>→</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"script\">E</mi><mo mathvariant=\"script\" lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\phi,\\psi: \\mathcal{E} \\to \\mathcal{E&#x27;}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ϕ</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">ψ</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.08944em;\">E</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7519em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.08944em;\">E</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7519em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> you can similarly show that <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ϕ</mi><mo>≅</mo><mi>ψ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\phi \\cong \\psi</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ϕ</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≅</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">ψ</span></span></span></span> as soon as <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ϕ</mi><mo>∘</mo><msub><mi>i</mi><mi>X</mi></msub><mo>≅</mo><mi>ψ</mi><mo>∘</mo><msub><mi>i</mi><mi>X</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\phi\\circ i_X \\cong \\psi\\circ i_X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ϕ</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∘</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8095em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3283em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≅</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">ψ</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∘</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8095em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3283em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> for all objects <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span>.</p>",
        "id": 547790391,
        "sender_full_name": "Jens Hemelaer",
        "timestamp": 1761763782
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ok, this doesn't seem to work... there is no geometric morphism <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>i</mi><mi>X</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">i_X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8095em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3283em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> in general the way I described it.</p>",
        "id": 547797367,
        "sender_full_name": "Jens Hemelaer",
        "timestamp": 1761766242
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Errol Yuksel gave a talk at CT last year where he claimed to have proven this theorem.</p>",
        "id": 548011018,
        "sender_full_name": "Ivan Di Liberti",
        "timestamp": 1761850033
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"277318\">Ivan Di Liberti</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/229136-theory.3A-category-theory/topic/Proof.20that.20locales.20gives.20a.20separating.20family.20in.20topoi/near/548011018\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Errol Yuksel gave a talk at CT last year where he claimed to have proven this theorem.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Do you mean this talk <a href=\"https://xabier.garcia.martinez.webs.uvigo.gal/CT2024/files/Slides/Yuksel_Slides.pdf\">https://xabier.garcia.martinez.webs.uvigo.gal/CT2024/files/Slides/Yuksel_Slides.pdf</a> ?</p>\n<p>If so, that seems the same proof as usual, where one has to find some localic topos with a map of effective descent to the classifying topos of the one object theory. That’s exactly what I'm trying to avoid.</p>\n<p>Btw, I briefly talked to him last year at the topos conference about a sketch of a proof I had of a higher version of Joyal-Tierney. I recall he was trying to prove some version of JT for ionads.</p>",
        "id": 548041955,
        "sender_full_name": "Fernando Yamauti",
        "timestamp": 1761863050
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What I'm after could be something along the lines of what <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"282722\">@Jens Hemelaer</span> was suggesting: some canonically defined maximal atlas instead of a specific atlas constructed in a somewhat intrincate way.</p>",
        "id": 548042809,
        "sender_full_name": "Fernando Yamauti",
        "timestamp": 1761863483
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>No, I do not mean that. I meant this one: <a href=\"https://archive.math.muni.cz/conference/ct2025/data/uploads/abstracts/yuksel.pdf\">https://archive.math.muni.cz/conference/ct2025/data/uploads/abstracts/yuksel.pdf</a></p>",
        "id": 548122247,
        "sender_full_name": "Ivan Di Liberti",
        "timestamp": 1761906403
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"277318\">Ivan Di Liberti</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/229136-theory.3A-category-theory/topic/Proof.20that.20locales.20gives.20a.20separating.20family.20in.20topoi/near/548122247\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>No, I do not mean that. I meant this one: <a href=\"https://archive.math.muni.cz/conference/ct2025/data/uploads/abstracts/yuksel.pdf\">https://archive.math.muni.cz/conference/ct2025/data/uploads/abstracts/yuksel.pdf</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Ah! So not last year's CT! Admittedly almost though! </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://archive.math.muni.cz/conference/ct2025/data/uploads/slides/yuksel.pdf\">Here are the slides</a> if anyone is interested</p>\n<p>Thanks for the pointer. He still relies on JT's covering though to prove that the maximal covering does the job. The improvement of Moerdijk-Vermeulen (which I was unaware of) is that open surjections are also lax effective epis (so we get a <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(2, 2)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>-sheaf besides a <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(2, 1)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>-sheaf). </p>\n<p>Btw, MW's result on the slides (I have yet to check the original paper though), then, imply that the topos associated to a specific localic category coincides with the topos associated to the groupoid completion of such localic cat.</p>",
        "id": 548231523,
        "sender_full_name": "Fernando Yamauti",
        "timestamp": 1761938879
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"557567\">Fernando Yamauti</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/229136-theory.3A-category-theory/topic/Proof.20that.20locales.20gives.20a.20separating.20family.20in.20topoi/near/548231523\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"277318\">Ivan Di Liberti</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/229136-theory.3A-category-theory/topic/Proof.20that.20locales.20gives.20a.20separating.20family.20in.20topoi/near/548122247\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>No, I do not mean that. I meant this one: <a href=\"https://archive.math.muni.cz/conference/ct2025/data/uploads/abstracts/yuksel.pdf\">https://archive.math.muni.cz/conference/ct2025/data/uploads/abstracts/yuksel.pdf</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Ah! So not last year's CT! Admittedly almost though! </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://archive.math.muni.cz/conference/ct2025/data/uploads/slides/yuksel.pdf\">Here are the slides</a> if anyone is interested</p>\n<p>Thanks for the pointer. He still relies on JT's covering though to prove that the maximal covering does the job. The improvement of Moerdijk-Vermeulen (which I was unaware of) is that open surjections are also lax effective epis (so we get a <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(2, 2)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>-sheaf besides a <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(2, 1)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>-sheaf). </p>\n<p>Btw, MW's result on the slides (I have yet to check the original paper though), then, imply that the topos associated to a specific localic category coincides with the topos associated to the groupoid completion of such localic cat.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yes, I think this was perhaps what I was alluding to during my QA at Octoberfest. We can 'get' the localic category of a bounded topos via the 2-structure of the 2-category of toposes.</p>\n<p>As to the main question: can we avoid the standard `localic cover + descent' argument and still get full &amp; faithful representation of geometric morphisms ? I think this results needs the toposes to be bounded (would we really expect it for elementary toposes?). </p>\n<p>Once we have the bound in our topos F, then we have  a localic effective descent morphism: W-&gt;&gt;1 where W=[N-&gt;&gt;B], i.e. surjections from the naturals to the bound (in F). This is enough to get that Loc_F = [G,Loc] (+) so you can get the result without topos-theoretic descent, but obviously at the cost of needing localic descent - so I don't think we can avoid some sort of descent argument to get there. </p>\n<p>(+) <a href=\"http://www.christophertownsend.org/Documents/LOCALIC_PROOF_LOCALIC_GROUPOID_GROTH_20111018.pdf\">http://www.christophertownsend.org/Documents/LOCALIC_PROOF_LOCALIC_GROUPOID_GROTH_20111018.pdf</a></p>",
        "id": 548284495,
        "sender_full_name": "Christopher Townsend",
        "timestamp": 1761982748
    }
]